The role of play and make believe in human cognitive development is a fundamental way in which we develop into well rounded and coherent adults. Being able to test out dreams, curiosities and scenarios is the main way in which we develop a solid ethical framework. 

That many of these role plays involve murder, violence or death (soldiers, cowboys and indians, doctor and nurses) is a point of constant fascination for me, as the use of children and nostalgia as a recurring theme in my work shows. My intent is always to question and interrogate the normal narratives we associate with these memories and stories that we tell ourselves, and to interrupt them subtly to try to reveal something more universal, within the human condition, that lies beneath
